```

**Key design notes:**
- Uses inline `style` for colors sourced from `BUILT_IN_THEMES[id].colors` — not from CSS variables — so all 3 cards always display their own colors regardless of which theme is currently active on `<html>`.
- The "Active" badge background uses an 8-digit hex alpha trick (`${c.accent}22` = 13% opacity) which works in all modern browsers and avoids an extra dependency.
- Uses `cn()` from `~/lib/utils` for conditional class composition, consistent with every other component in this codebase.
- No local state — reads from `useTheme()`.
- `aria-checked` / `role="radio"` / `role="radiogroup"` is consistent with the existing radio pattern in `_chat.settings.tsx`.

---

### Step 6: Update `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx`

Three changes are needed in this file:

**A. Remove the `THEME_OPTIONS` constant** (lines 25–41). It is no longer needed.

**B. Replace the `useTheme` destructuring** — change from:

```ts
const { theme, setTheme, resolvedTheme } = useTheme();
```

to:

```ts
const { themeId, resolvedTheme } = useTheme();
```

`setTheme` is no longer needed directly in this component since `ThemeSelector` calls `setThemeId` internally.

**C. Replace the Appearance section body** — remove the `role="radiogroup"` div with the `.map(THEME_OPTIONS)` loop (lines 210–238) and the paragraph below it (lines 240–243), and replace with:

```tsx
import { ThemeSelector } from "../components/ThemeSelector";

// ...inside the Appearance section, after the <div className="mb-4"> block:

<ThemeSelector />

<p className="mt-4 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
  Active theme:{" "}
  <span className="font-medium text-foreground">{resolvedTheme}</span>
